        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-06-01 13:37:57.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1:\n> > \n> > There seems to be one from Kevin, https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/logging-analytics/+/102099\n> > \n> > Kevin can you confirm if the fix is expected to be included in Frankfurt release ?\n> \n> I'll just update the version.  This needs to move forward.\n\nStrike that last comment.  That version change should be done in a separate change to the master branch so that it is not lost. If we truly need it in Frankfurt, we can cherry pick it, but ONLY if it is to\ncorrect a High or Highest severity defect tracked by ONAP integration - no other changes are permitted at this late stage.\n\nThe scope of this change is merely a version roll of our code. No other changes should be included - since that version roll is branch specific.",
